## Consequences

### Positive

- Clear conventions reduce onboarding time for new developers
- Static analysis (PHPStan level 8) catches type errors before they reach production
- Documentation-first approach (architecture.md, api-conventions.md, ADRs) supports long-term maintainability
- Test strategy ({{ test_strategy }}) is defined upfront, preventing coverage debt

### Negative

- More initial setup than a minimal Symfony skeleton
- Symfony {{ symfony_version }} requires PHP {{ php_version }}+ which may not be available in all environments
{% if use_ddd %}
- DDD layers add file count and require discipline to maintain boundaries
{% endif %}
{% if api_style == "api-platform" %}
- API Platform has a significant learning curve for developers new to the resource/operation model
{% endif %}

### Risks

- Technology choices are opinionated; future contributors must read this ADR before proposing alternatives
- PHPStan level 8 may require extra work when integrating third-party libraries with incomplete type coverage

